# Mutter (Cursor)

Read `.mutter/core/project.md` before substantive work.

## Rules

- Use `.mutter/index/` for navigation; never load the whole repository into context.
- Obey `.mutter/rules/` and `.mutter/architecture/` for boundaries and ADRs.
- Use `.mutter/workflows/` for repeatable procedures.
- Prefer incremental reads: only files tied to the active task, plan, or scan delta.
- Before **web search** for official language/framework/database documentation, check **`.mutter/memory/official-tech-docs-roadmap.md`** for a direct link (read one section only).
- Keep **this rule file small**; bulk knowledge lives under `.mutter/`.

## Plugin alignment

When the **Mutter** Cursor plugin is installed, use its skills/commands for Mutter workflows. In **Claude Code**, the same workflows are **`/mutter:<skill>`** (e.g. `/mutter:scan`). In Cursor, use palette commands (**mutter-scan**, **mutter-task**, **mutter-prd**, **mutter-status**, **mutter-agent-cadence**, …) or ask the agent to follow the matching skill.

When **`scripts/mutter.py`** exists at the repo root: at **session resume** or before **execute/continue** on tasks, run **`python3 scripts/mutter.py status`**; for the canonical *when to run which CLI* map, run **`python3 scripts/mutter.py agent-cadence`** (optional **`--out .mutter/context/agent-cadence.md`**). Full index: **`/mutter:help`** (Claude) or **mutter-help** / **help** skill (Cursor).

## Safety

- No dumping unrelated modules, generated artifacts, or entire frameworks into chat.
- After material changes, update `.mutter/tasks/`, `.mutter/architecture/decisions.md`, and scan metadata as appropriate.

_Upstream **mutter** does not commit `.cursor/`; harness docs live in **`docs/mutter-plugin-harness-reference.md`**._
